<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<%- include('../partials/nav') %>

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="narrow text-center">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center">Security &amp; trust</span>
      <h1>Engineered to be trusted — and hardened for real</h1>
      <p class="lead">The security posture below is presented as a design showcase. Where it describes app-level protections, those protections are genuinely implemented in this build.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-3 mt-4">
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <%- include('../partials/icon', { name: 'key' }) %>
        <h3 class="mt-2">Credentials, hashed</h3>
        <p>Passwords are stored as salted bcrypt hashes — never in plain text. A password policy enforces length and character variety.</p>
        <span class="pill pill-up"><span class="dot"></span>Implemented</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <%- include('../partials/icon', { name: 'lock' }) %>
        <h3 class="mt-2">Two-factor authentication</h3>
        <p>Optional TOTP-based 2FA (Google Authenticator / Authy compatible), with a QR enrolment flow and step-tolerant verification.</p>
        <span class="pill pill-up"><span class="dot"></span>Implemented</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <%- include('../partials/icon', { name: 'shield' }) %>
        <h3 class="mt-2">CSRF &amp; strict CSP</h3>
        <p>Every state-changing request carries a CSRF token. A strict Content-Security-Policy blocks inline and third-party scripts.</p>
        <span class="pill pill-up"><span class="dot"></span>Implemented</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <%- include('../partials/icon', { name: 'pulse' }) %>
        <h3 class="mt-2">Rate-limited endpoints</h3>
        <p>Authentication and money-movement routes are rate-limited to blunt brute-force and abuse, with a global baseline limiter on top.</p>
        <span class="pill pill-up"><span class="dot"></span>Implemented</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <%- include('../partials/icon', { name: 'user' }) %>
        <h3 class="mt-2">Session integrity</h3>
        <p>Secure, httpOnly, sameSite session cookies. Sessions regenerate on login to prevent fixation, and you can revoke other active sessions.</p>
        <span class="pill pill-up"><span class="dot"></span>Implemented</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <%- include('../partials/icon', { name: 'check' }) %>
        <h3 class="mt-2">Input validation &amp; safe queries</h3>
        <p>All form input is validated and sanitised; all database access uses parameterised prepared statements — no SQL-injection surface.</p>
        <span class="pill pill-up"><span class="dot"></span>Implemented</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-2 mt-4" style="align-items:start">
      <div class="card card-pad">
        <span class="pill pill-info"><span class="dot"></span>Illustrative posture</span>
        <h3 class="mt-2">Custody, KYC &amp; compliance messaging</h3>
        <p>A production platform of this kind would describe cold-storage custody, segregated client accounts, KYC/AML onboarding and independent audits. In this trial those are <strong>presentation only</strong> — the onboarding “verification” auto-approves and verifies nothing against any real identity service.</p>
        <ul class="text-muted small" style="padding-left:18px">
          <li>Simulated KYC (ID upload UI + personal info) — stored, not verified</li>
          <li>Cold-storage / segregated-custody copy — illustrative</li>
          <li>“Regulated / audited” badges — illustrative, not real certifications</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card card-pad" style="border-color:rgba(216,178,90,0.28);background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(216,178,90,0.08), var(--bg-2))">
        <h3>Deployment assumptions</h3>
        <p>For a real deployment this build assumes:</p>
        <ul class="text-muted small" style="padding-left:18px">
          <li>HTTPS-only — secure cookies are enabled in production</li>
          <li>A trusted reverse proxy terminating TLS</li>
          <li>Secrets (session secret, DB path) supplied via environment</li>
          <li>Security headers via Helmet, including HSTS behind HTTPS</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="disclaimer-strong mt-2"><%= brand.disclaimer %></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
